<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SHIFT CONTROL LINKAGE WITH MANUAL TRANSMISSION - SERVICE
        PROCEDURES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>SERVICE PROCEDURES</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
            <title>CONTROL LINKAGE</title>
            <para>Servicing the shift control linkage consists of removing any worn or damaged parts and replacing them
                with new parts.
            </para>
            <para>At time of assembly, lubricate linkage components (refer to
                <hotlnk document="s13004_2.xml" xrefid="hl1300402">MAINTENANCE
                    <xref refid="hl1300402"/>
                </hotlnk>
                ).
            </para>
            <para>When assembling the control selection lever (Item 4,
                <hotlnk document="s13004_1.xml" xrefid="f1300407">Figure 7</hotlnk>) to the remote control outer shift
                lever (Item 5,
                <hotlnk document="s13004_1.xml" xrefid="f1300407">Figure 7</hotlnk>), be sure to use the proper hole in
                the shift lever. Use the
                <emph type="bold">upper hole for Fuller</emph>
                transmissions and the
                <emph type="bold">lower hole for Spicer</emph>.
            </para>
            <para>When assembling the pivot rod (Item 3) to the control rod selection lever (Item 4), use the lower hole
                in the selection lever for all transmissions.
            </para>
            <para>Adjust the control linkage as described in
                <hotlnk document="s13004_4.xml" xrefid="hl1300403">ADJUSTMENT
                    <xref refid="hl1300403"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
            <para>Tighten the mounting hardware as specified in the
                <hotlnk document="s13004_9.xml" xrefid="hl1300404">TORQUE CHART
                    <xref refid="hl1300404"/>
                </hotlnk>
                .
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
